        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 6:57PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 656 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Whitehorse Butte, or 25 miles west of Owyhee, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibility. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Juniper Basin Reservoir around 700 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
